JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba says government has estimated how much is needed to fund President Jacob Zuma’s plan to scrap tuition fees for poor students. Treasury’s still figuring out how it will fund the plan. READ: Treasury reviewing Zuma's free higher education proposal Gigaba will provide specific details in his budget speech on the 21 February, but admits it’ll be a tough balancing act. In December President Zuma announced free education for students coming from poor households. eNCA